        "value": 30,
        "unit": "W",
        "description": "Typical range for ns-pulsed Nd:YAG lasers in semiconductor cleaning to balance efficiency and avoid thermal damage to InP (melting point ~1062°C, moderate reflectivity at 1064 nm). Recommended starting at 30W for light contamination; max safe below 100W to prevent substrate ablation. Source: Manufacturer specs from IPG Photonics and Coherent for industrial cleaners; ablation studies in J. Appl. Phys. (e.g., InP thresholds imply power limits)."
